    <h2 class="sect-title">About North Haven Upper</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Established back in 1977, the North Haven Upper is a part of the North Haven community and is separated from the Lower North Haven by a bus trap.</p>
            <p class="par-xl">Bordered on the west by one of Canadaâ€™s largest municipal reserve, the Nose Hill Park, the community in the North Haven Upper is located at a convenient distance from a variety of public amenities and recreational venues.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Homes for sale in North Haven Upper comprise a wide selection of housing options ranging from 2-storey split level homes to luxurious bungalows and condominiums, with a typical residential unit listed at an average price of $460,000.</p>
